-
-Infer budget mode unless the user specifies it.
-
-- `balanced` default.
-- `cheap` when user emphasizes low cost, bulk edits, simple tasks, or API-credit conservation.
-- `premium` when user emphasizes maximum quality, production risk, architecture, security, high ambiguity, or prior failures.
-- `local-first` when user emphasizes privacy, offline, local host, no cloud, or local-only constraints.
-
-Budget mode never overrides safety. High/Critical work must escalate even in cheap or local-first mode.
